target.comment:
1500 weapons confiscated by Kosovo Police and publicly destroyed in a transparent manner;
All imported weapons aimed at the civilian market were import marked in accordance to relevant international regulations;
75% of all tracing requests were resolved.
75% of relevant GoK actors trained and certified in relevant SALW issues.
Targeted communities understand the methodology of monitoring tensions in their communities and are further implementing crime audits to be used for prevention.
5% increase in safety perception of citizens in the selected communities.

iati-activity.description:
Award covers three outputs to support:
Reintegration of returnees;
Self-reliance of RAE;
Law on Language Use.

actual.comment:
Department of Industry designed Annual Report of Industrial Development and contributed to drafting Tourism Development Strategy, Two-year action plan for Division of Tourism and a thorough Assessment Report for Division of Tourism; 
Tourism sector in ERS enhanced and knowledge of 139 businesses on exporting requirements and environment protection improved;
36 new jobs created (89% women).

target.comment:
Target 1.1. 39 Municipal staff from the relevant departments in the two Municipalities are trained;

Target 3.1  One Audit Report and TEPs are prepared for each Municipality;
Target 3.2. At least 20 women and men are trained through several intervention lines;
Target 3.3: At least 75 micro enterprises are upgraded;
Target 3.4: Three organizations are identified;

actual.comment:
Result 1.1. In total, 155 municipal staff trained in economic and rural development activities & human rights-based approach to service delivery in 2014; More specifically,16 (4 women, 12 men) municipal officials from Štrpce/Shtërpcë municipality participated in IADK trainings; 62 (21 women, 41 men) municipal officials participated in MDA trainings; 5 municipal officials from Dragash/Dragaš municipality participated in IADK trainings; 72 (10 women and 62 men) municipal officials participated in MDA trainings.  (Sources: IADK and MDA final reports). 

Result 3.1. A Territorial Audit was conducted and a TEP for each municipality formulated, finalized and signed by all relevant stakeholders;
Result 3.2. 23 candidates (18 men and 5 women) are being trained under the TEP Action no.2. (The VTC trainings to be completed by February 2015). (Source: Project documentation); 
Result 3.3. 30 beneficiaries (28 men and 2 women) from Dragash/Dragaš Municipality have benefited from TEP Action no. 1, with 1 cow and 1 milking machine; 54 farmers with 2-20 cows benefited a milking machine (52 men and 2 women), and 15 to 20 of these farmers are pre-identified to be included in the milk collection system; In total, 84 rural micro-enterprises upgraded during 2014(Source: Project documentation);
Result 3.4. Three NGOs/Social Enterprises identified and established, Business Plans  concluded, their project proposals submitted and approved and the first installment  allocated to them for operational activities.
